Hi all -

I'm new to Verilog and HDL in general. I've worked on a few designs which were simulated using VCS from edaplayground and am now trying to move to Verilator.

If I want to put together a testbench in verilog which changes signal after 3 and 5 clock cycles, I can do the following:

```
initial begin
  #3;
  rst = 1;
  #2;
  rst = 0;
  ...
end

```

To achieve the same thing with Verilator, I'm trying to do it the following way:

```
top->clk = 0;
time_counter = 0;
while (time_counter < 100) {
  // Since each loop is a half cycle, 3 cycles is at counter=6
  if (time_counter == 6) {
     top->rst = 1;
  }

  if (time_counter == 10) {
     top->rst = 0;
  }

  top->clk = !top->clk;
  top->eval();
  tfp->dump(time_counter);
  time_counter++;
}

```

But very soon this becomes really cumbersome esp if I'm trying to test a UART which needs to be done at a different clock frequency than the main core.

My question is - am I doing this right? Or is there another way to achieve this?

Thanks in advance!

